The paper discusses the use of deep reinforcement learning techniques to optimize the cooling system of a simulated data center. This involves the use of machine learning algorithms to control power consumption, which falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the control of a complex system, which falls under the category of control systems, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the optimization of power consumption, which falls under the category of distributed computing, making cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of deep reinforcement learning techniques, which falls under the category of neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible sub-category.
